align=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  An option for us mages.</span><hr size=1> Ok so this board is now full of rants and gripes.  Is that all we mages do now is complain?  Well its time to try and stop that.  I have an small idea to try and help fix that.  I would like EVERYONE here to post ONE point of mages that they would like to fix or adapt and only one point please.  On march first i will tally all the responces and add a vote topic for the top 5.  On april first i will pick the one with the most votes and then ask that everyone endorse it with thier name and server. On may First i will send an Email to VI, and a Feedback with everyones name and server name and the point of interest that we as mages wish to have attended.<br>
<br>
I will start with my point that i would like to see.  I would like to see frenzied burnout into a semi permenent skill (short recast time with a long duration)<br>
<br>
PS  PLEASE only put VIABLE ideas here.  They have already said they have addressed pathing issues so i think something like that would be a mute point.<br>
<br>
PPS  Would a Moderate stick this to the top of the forum here by chance. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uutaelr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Utaelr</A> at: 1/28/02 11:48:18 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usiadhail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siadhail</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/02 9:12:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Enough is enough</span><hr size=1> Give our pets the hybrid treatment. They melee and cast spells. Do not interrupt their melee while they cast. It would be a small but I think effective step in nudging their melee power up a bit. This is taken from a low level (30's) mages point of view but i have noticed people saying that MS pets sometimes work nice because they do not cast and waste time on easily resisted spells. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufandarian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fandarian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/02 9:17:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Enough is enough</span><hr size=1> Higher level pets.  Not necessarily harder hitting pets, but higher level.  So they hit more reliably. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=29794">Fandarian</a>
<BR>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65959">Timoni</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unandail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nandail</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 218<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/02 9:43:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Enough is enough</span><hr size=1> There have been lots of these topics rescently, with lots of great ideas.<br>
<br>
I guess I fail to see the point of trying to come up with a solution again when we are still viewed as overbalanced.<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
Nandail<br>
55th Mage on Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujochangaladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/02 10:14:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Enough is enough</span><hr size=1>     Increase either pet dps or hit points, or simply increase their ability to hit reliably. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udarkclawthedarkavenger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkclaw The Dark Avenger</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/02 12:02:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  ...</span><hr size=1> All I want is very simple...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1. Pathing problems solved</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- However this takes an awful long time to do, so Verant would be better off just giving us these 2 things.<br>
<br>
A) /pet hold command<br>
B) <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet drag</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> A.K.A Summon Companion (NO casting time and NO mana needed)<br>
<br>
That would take care of the pathing problem easily.<br>
<br>
- Pet never aggros anything, nothing aggros pet.<br>
- Pet can come to your side easily because it's never fighting something it aggroed, and even if it did wander off, just press /pet drag and pet comes to you AT ONCE (no casting time)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2. Higher level pets</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- There's not even a need to raise the pet's melee dmg or it's delay. Not even a need for more HP. Just make the pet the same lvl as the caster (or A FEW lvls lower - NOT a few DOZEN /sigh)<br>
<br>
This way pet would actually hit something.<br>
<br>
There you go. That alone would solve any Magician's problem to get a group ever again, and it would actually help us when soloing, because pets can actually hit the mob!<br>
<br>
Plain and simple, and it can be done in 1 patch EASILY. Would hardly take any work.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uutaelr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Utaelr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/02 12:04:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ...</span><hr size=1> so Darkclaw which of the two would you want for your vote?  1 or 2? (remember i am not going to address pathing problems with them for the reason that it has no chance of them doing anything about it) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udarkclawthedarkavenger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkclaw The Dark Avenger</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/02 12:09:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  ...</span><hr size=1> If I had to pick the one it'd help me the most it would be definetly number 1.<br>
<br>
Why?? <br>
<br>
Well, our pets would be useless still in high end raids, but at least I'd have him up!!! And by simply commanding my pet to attack, and then back off, and all, would make me a happier player.<br>
<br>
Really, I created my mage to USE my pet. To have him up at all times. Just seeing him FIGHTING (even though he doesn't do much) makes me happy.<br>
<br>
Plus, there's the old debate here. If a mage gets jumped in a dungeon when his pet is gone = dead mage.<br>
<br>
Now if pet is up and mage gets up, well, Jabantik can tank enough, so I'd have time to get a gate out.<br>
<br>
All I want (and probably every other mage) is to have my pet with me in raids. He doesn't even need to be the biggest dmg dealer. I don't even have to be the biggest dmg dealer class in game. Pet just needs to with us. That's what separates us from other casters.<br>
<br>
So yeah, number 1 definetly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umalchite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malchite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/02 1:04:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Taunting</span><hr size=1>   I would choose MAGE pets with better taunting, I find it impossible to solo anything unless my earth pet can root it.<br>
<br>
Malchite Manastorm (Lany's T'vl)<br>
Mage of the 36 summon<br>
